headline: 3 Low-Volatility Stocks We Keep Off Our Radar
summary: A stock with low volatility can be reassuring, but it doesn’t always mean strong long-term performance. Investors who prioritize stability may miss out on higher-reward opportunities elsewhere.

headline: 3 Reasons K is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since February 2025, Kellanova has been in a holding pattern, posting a small loss of 2.6% while floating around $80.07. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 5.3% gain during that period.
